ecifically on issues such as the politics of birth control, the classification of sexual "deviance," debates over homosexuality and feminism, and the role of sexuality in our own new world of post-modern spirituality, consumer capitalism, and the Internet.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aLibertyxMiscellaneaxHistory. 0aMagicxHistoryxWestern countries. 0aMagiczWestern countriesxHistory. 0aSexxMiscellaneaxHistoryxWestern countries. 0aSexzWestern countriesvMiscellaneaxHistory. 0aSexzWestern countriesxMiscellaneaxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh  aacademia about magic.  aaleister crowley.  aamerican spiritualists.  aanton lavey.  abuddhism.  aconsumer capitalism.  aeastern traditions.  afeminism.  agerald gardner.  ahinduism.  ahugh urban.  ajulius evola.  akahhalah.  algbtq.  amagic and witches.  apaschal beverly randolph.  apost-modern spirituality.  aqueer studies.  asexual deviance.  asexual magic.  asexuality.  aspirituality and the occult.  atantra.  atantric sex.  awestern esoteric traditions.  awicca and witchcraft.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093288340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520932883423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520932883/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles